50|$|When regnal {{numbering}} of <b>the</b> <b>Popes</b> {{began to}} be used, Antipope Felix II was counted as one of <b>the</b> <b>Popes</b> of that name. <b>The</b> second true <b>Pope</b> Felix is thus known by the number III, and <b>the</b> true third <b>Pope</b> Felix was given the number IV. This custom also affected the name taken by Antipope Felix V, {{who would have been}} <b>the</b> fourth <b>Pope</b> Felix.|$|R
50|$|The {{temporal}} {{power of}} <b>the</b> <b>popes</b> is <b>the</b> political and secular governmental activity of <b>the</b> <b>popes</b> of <b>the</b> Roman Catholic Church, as distinguished from their spiritual and pastoral activity.|$|R
