50|$|After gaining magical {{power through}} his {{pact with the}} Devil, Doctor Faustus - as {{depicted}} in Christopher Marlowe's play - travels to Rome. Armed with his new powers and attended by Mephastophilis, he goes to <b>the</b> <b>Pope’s</b> court, makes himself invisible, and plays a series of tricks. He disrupts <b>the</b> <b>Pope’s</b> banquet by stealing food and boxing <b>the</b> <b>Pope’s</b> ears http://www.sparknotes.com/lit/doctorfaustus/summary.html.|$|R
